{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17516867","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17516867"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T13:47:40+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T13:47:40+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12725"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"12725","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/12725"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.03,0.56,0.21,0.01,0.19]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5180"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"110711"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"5180","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/5180"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12725"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92959"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"108"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"1087"},{"type":"tags","id":"2173"},{"type":"tags","id":"2545"},{"type":"tags","id":"3549"},{"type":"tags","id":"8118"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"8775"},{"type":"contributions","id":"8803"},{"type":"contributions","id":"14791"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"110711","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/110711"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 28-year-old man presents with a cough, loss of weight, night-sweats and a low-grade fever. The patient has stated that he has smoked one pack of cigarettes everyday since he was 15 years old; he also has noted that, when he is stressed, he tends to smoke as much two packs in a single day. Three months ago he returned from a six month work secondment in Nepal.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he has fingernail clubbing, diminished breath sounds and enlarged cervical lymph nodes. A chest X-ray shows bilateral pleural effusions and hilar lymphadenopathy. Gram staining of a sputum sample is conducted, but there are no signs that there are any gram positive or gram negative organisms.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Pneumocystis jirovecii","Tuberculosis","Small cell lung cancer","Influenza","Sarcoidosis"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis question requires recognising that this patient is most likely to have \u003Cstrong\u003Etuberculosis (TB),\u003C/strong\u003E as indicated by; coughing, loss of weight, night-sweats, low-grade fever, fingernail clubbing, diminished breath sounds, enlarged cervical lymph nodes, pleural effusions, hilar lymphadenopathy, and a lack of gram positivity/gram negativity on staining. He has also spent time working in a part of the world where tuberculosis is endemic. Tuberculosis is acid-fast as per Ziehl\u2013Neelsen staining. Sputum testing, endobronchial ultrasound-guided transbronchial needle aspiration, and culturing could all be useful in confirming the diagnosis of TB (this would be important to do before commencing treatment).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile the patient has weight loss and is a smoker, \u003Cstrong\u003Esmall cell lung cancer\u003C/strong\u003E is less likely based on the X-ray findings. For this patient, while the lung issues may be consistent with \u003Cstrong\u003Esarcoidosis\u003C/strong\u003E, the additional systemic symptoms are far less likely to occur with sarcoidosis. When systemic symptoms do occur with sarcoidosis, they tend to be those of fever, anorexia, and arthralgia, seen in about 45% of cases.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere is no indication that the patient is immunocompromised, and hence, this is less likely to be \u003Cstrong\u003Epneumocystis jirovecii. \u003C/strong\u003EThough viral causes may be worthwhile to be considered for this case as the gram staining does not show a gram positive or negative organism, the overall presentation is less likely to occur with \u003Cstrong\u003Einfluenza.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Pulmonary tuberculosis manifests with systemic symptoms, as well specific respiratory symptoms and findings"],"references":["Queensland Health. Treatment of tuberculosis in adults and children. Guideline Version 3.0. [Internet] 2021. [updated 2021 March; cited 2023 April 11]. Available from: https://www.health.qld.gov.au/__data/assets/pdf_file/0029/444566/tb-guideline-treatment.pdf","Jilani TN, Avula A, Zafar Gondal A, et al. Active Tuberculosis. [Updated 2023 Jan 26]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. 2023. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK513246/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92959"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12725"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92959","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/92959"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-08-03T18:53:13+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-08-03T18:53:13+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5180"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"110711"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"11","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec1","name":"Respiratory Medicine","synonyms":["Pulmonology"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"